\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the operational framework for monitoring,
 measuring,
 and reporting on the Information Operations Department's adherence to the service level commitments defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Service Catalog and SLA Policy).
 This policy governs the in-flight collection of service performance data,
 the thresholds and protocols that trigger corrective action when commitments are at risk,
 and the reporting cadence through which performance data is surfaced to the IT Director and,
 ultimately,
 to the organizational performance management function defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Performance Metrics and Operational KPIs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy is concerned with operational execution:
 whether commitments are being met,
 when and how deviations are detected,
 and what happens next.
 It does not redefine SLA targets (
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
),
 establish the broader KPI taxonomy (
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
),
 or govern the audit and self-assessment functions that verify long-term compliance (
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
).
\end_layout

