\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the approving authority for service level performance reports and any corrective action plans arising from sustained SLA non-compliance.
 Shall review monthly performance summary reports prepared by the Assistant IT Director.
 Shall authorize any formal deviation from reporting cadences or data collection standards established in this policy.
 Shall ensure that performance data generated under this policy is integrated with the quarterly KPI review process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the primary operational owner of the service level management and reporting function.
 Shall ensure that performance data is collected continuously and accurately from the work order system and any supporting monitoring tools.
 Shall monitor SLA adherence across all open and closed work orders no less than weekly.
 Shall prepare and distribute the reports defined in Section 6.4.
 Shall identify deviations meeting the thresholds defined in Section 6.3,
 document them in the work order system,
 and initiate the prescribed escalation or corrective action response.
 Shall ensure that vendor SLA performance is tracked and reported in accordance with Section 6.5.
 Shall prepare the quarterly performance data summary submitted to the IT Director for integration with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 reporting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Department Personnel (All Tiers)
\series default
:
 Shall document all triage decisions,
 reclassifications,
 remediation milestones,
 escalation actions,
 and closure decisions in the work order system in sufficient detail to support accurate SLA adherence measurement.
 Shall notify the Assistant IT Director promptly when a work order is at risk of missing a response or resolution commitment.
 Shall cooperate with data collection and reporting activities as directed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Department Heads
\series default
:
 Shall review service level performance summaries for services used by their departments when distributed by the Assistant IT Director.
 Shall communicate service delivery concerns to the Assistant IT Director through the work order system or direct written correspondence.
\end_layout

