Vendor Performance Tracking
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a vendor SLA performance record for each IT-Supported and Vendor-Managed asset with contractual service level terms.
 This record shall be maintained in the IT Asset Catalog entry for the applicable asset in Redmine and shall capture:
 (a) contracted response and resolution commitments;
 (b) each vendor escalation event,
 including the timestamp IT initiated contact,
 the timestamp vendor acknowledged,
 and the timestamp vendor resolved or reported status;
 and (c) a running compliance calculation for each vendor across the current contract period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor Breach Recording
\series default
:
 A vendor SLA breach shall be recorded when a vendor fails to meet a contracted response or resolution commitment.
 Vendor breaches are separate from IT SLA breaches but shall be included in the monthly performance summary required by Section 6.4.
 Vendor breach records shall be preserved for the duration of the applicable contract plus three (3) years and shall be made available to the IT Director and,
 where applicable,
