\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Recurring Ticket Analysis and Upward Reporting Integration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Recurring Ticket Identification
\series default
:
 Consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\series default

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 a work order shall be flagged as a Recurring Ticket when the same user experiences the same issue within any rolling ninety (90) calendar day window and a prior work order for that issue was closed as resolved.
 The Assistant IT Director shall review the work order system monthly to identify recurring ticket patterns and shall ensure that all Recurring Tickets are flagged in the system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Root Cause Assignment
\series default
:
 Each Recurring Ticket flag shall trigger assignment of a root cause determination by the Assistant IT Director or delegated technician.
 Root cause determinations shall be documented in the work order record within five (5) business days of the Recurring Ticket flag and shall classify the cause as one of the following:
 (a) user training or documentation gap,
 (b) unresolved underlying technical issue,
 (c) process failure,
 or (d) environmental or infrastructure condition.
 Root cause classifications shall be reported in the Monthly Performance Summary.
\end_layout

